					<p>Wilford Woodruff, center, became fourth President of the Church on 7 April 1889 and selected the counselors of his predecessor: First Counselor George Q. Cannon, right, and Second Counselor Joseph F. Smith, left.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		
                            
                            
                            
